description: Join the KAP GSO in celebrating the end of another year behind Loree Gym. We will grill, have games, and just relax. We recommend bringing your own folding chair. We will begin setting up at 3pm and probably have food ready about an hour after.

description: Join us on a visit to Rutgers Gardens on Friday, May 19th from11:30am-2:30pm. We will wind down and celebrate the end of the semester, enjoying food and the beautiful scenery! Meet us in the lot on log cabin road ( see address)!Please RSVP by Thursday at noonru.graduate.christian@gmail.comto let us know you are coming and if you need a ride!

description: Celebrate the end of the spring semester with MBGSO and Rutgers Seeding Labs. Join us to make your own Korean BBQ bowl, sip bubble tea and play some lawn games with your friends! In the event of rain, we will hold it in theDean's Conference Room 123.All grad students, postdocs and faculty are welcome to attend! Please RSVP.

name: Geology Club - General Interest Meeting Fall 2023
description: Welcome to the Geology Club! We are holding a General Interest Meeting in Room 231 of Wright Rieman Laboratories on Busch campus on Tuesday, September 12th at 7:00pm.Learn about all of the fun trips and cool events our club holds throughout the year, such as Grad Night, Career Night, trips to the Sterling Hill Mine Museum and other local geological spots. We also get involved in events with the Department of Earth and Planetary Sciences like the Oktoberfest, Holiday Party and more!We'll go on hiking trips, hold educational lectures, and bring students to the sectional and national GSA meetings to be exposed to the earth sciences!

name: Amnesty Introduction Meeting
description: The first general meeting of Rutgers Amnesty, where we will discuss the opportunities, events, and meetings planned for the upcoming fall semester! We will be introducing the eboard and what Amnesty International stands for and the work that is currently being undertaken for human rights.

name: General Interest Meeting
description: Join us for our 1st meeting of the 2023-2024 Academic Year! We are looking forward to meeting new and returning members for an exciting night of discussion, games and pizza. There will be prizes involved for the winners of our trivia.

description: With this being the first meeting of the academic year, RAHSA welcomes everyone to come and meet new and old members alike and to share in the joy of the study of art history! At this meeting we will have food and beverage as well as opportunities to learn more about future RAHSA events such as Museum trips, trivia, and button making!

name: Geology Club - Grad Night
description: The Geology Club is proud to present our annual Grad Night where we will be hosting a group of graduate students in the Earth and Planetary Sciences to talk to undergraduates. This is a great opportunity for students to get a sense of what graduate school and conducting research is like, as well as having the opportunity to ask questions about the graduate application process.Free pizza and refreshments will be provided by the Department of Earth and Planetary Sciences. This event will take place in Room 231 of Wright Rieman Laboratories on Busch Campus. All are welcome!

description: Meet your fellow UNICEFers in a fun social event: Paint and Sip with UNICEF.

organizationName: G. H. Cook Biochemistry & Microbiology Club
name: Finding Research at Rutgers
location: Merle V. Adams Room, Cook Student Center
description: Are you looking to get involved inresearch at Rutgers but don't know where to start? Attend this G.H. Cook Biochemistry and Microbiology Club meeting to hear from our officers and upperclassmen about the best ways to discover what you're interested in, reach out to professors, and start gaining experience in your field!This session will best serve students interested in biochemistry, microbiology, and other life sciences disciplines, but all majors are welcome to join and will gain something valuable.

organizationName: Ahmadiyya Muslim Students Association for Women
name: The Second Coming
description: This is an interfaith event around the topic of the second-coming of Jesus. We will be inviting people of different faiths to come talk about Jesus and his second coming. We will be inviting an Imam, Buddhist monk, Rabbi, Priest, and Hindu representative to this event to talk about the second coming of Jesus in their respective religions. Christians believe in the second coming of Jesus, Hindus believe in the second-coming of Jesus, Buddhist believe in the second coming of Maitreyu, and Ahmadiyyat has its own take of the second coming of Jesus. We will be discussing the similarities of our beliefs in this event in order to promote unity.

name: Halloween Celebration 2023
description: Come join us for fun game challenges, giveaways, cheap cosplay contest, and more! Show up with your Halloween costumes to celebrate Halloween at our annual Halloween event!

name: World's Finals Watch Party 2023
description: Come join other members to watch the World's Finals 2023 together! Enjoy food and drinks while watching the most exciting and competitive Esports grand finals of the year.

name: Commemorating the Bolshevik Revolution
description: This will a panel on the Bolshevik Revolution and its aftermath. We will be reflecting on the Bolshevik experience and synthesizing those experiences for today. We will be inviting several prominent historians as panelists.

organizationName: Ahmadiyya Muslim Students Association for Women
name: The Astonishing Life of Muhammad
description: Our goal for this event is to talk about the life and story of the prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him). We will be having multiple speakers talk about his life from birth to death as well as the legacy he left as the prophet. We also will be presenting insights into the story of the Prophet, which the world otherwise may not have known as well as a unique perspective in response to recent caricatures and ridicule.This is a coed event. People of allfaiths and races are welcome to come to the event. If you have any questions or concerns please reach out to us.It will take place on Wednesday, March 8th at 7pm in the Busch Student Center Multipurpose Room B. Inshallah we hope to see you all there! Please RSVP ahead of time using this link.https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSfUQXFAJAoHl2apUye6L2p8Av9BpjZjga7dJiIlJjYeijt7Cg/viewform
